ask: cdx_ehash NULL-guard ct deref in delete paths (audit B5)

AUDIT-cdx.md P0.03 — re-verifies prior audit C3.

Two flow-delete sites in cdx/cdx_ehash.c dereference the per-flow
hardware-classifier (ct) pointer without checking it for NULL after the
top-level entry NULL guard:

1) delete_entry_from_classif_table(): the existing
   "if (!entry) ... return FAILURE" gate does NOT validate entry->ct,
   yet the very next line does ExternalHashTableDeleteKey(entry->ct->td,
   entry->ct->index, entry->ct->handle). entry->ct can legitimately be
   NULL after a previous failed insert/delete cycle (the function
   itself sets entry->ct = NULL on the success path).

2) delete_pppoe_relay_entry_from_classif_table(): no entry NULL guard
   at all, then unconditionally reads entry->hw_entry.ct and
   dereferences it. entry==NULL or hw_entry.ct==NULL on a bridge teardown
   race produces a kernel oops.

Fix: extend the entry guard to "(!entry || !entry->ct)" in site 1; add
explicit "if (!entry) ... if (!ct)" gates in site 2 immediately before
the ct deref. No behaviour change on success paths.

Signed-off-by: ASK audit B5--- a/cdx_ehash.c
+++ b/cdx_ehash.c
@@ -474,7 +474,7 @@
 /* delete classif entry from table */
 int delete_entry_from_classif_table(PCtEntry entry)
 {
-	if (!entry)
+	if (!entry || !entry->ct)
 	{
 		DPA_ERROR("%s:: Ct entry is NULL\n", __FUNCTION__);
 		return FAILURE;
@@ -498,7 +498,12 @@
 {
 	struct hw_ct *ct;
 
+	/* B5 P0.03: NULL-guard entry and ct before deref */
+	if (!entry)
+		return FAILURE;
 	ct = entry->hw_entry.ct;
+	if (!ct)
+		return FAILURE;
 
 	CDX_DPA_DPRINT("\n");
 	if(ExternalHashTableDeleteKey(ct->td,ct->index, ct->handle))
